         <abstract>
            <p>Conditions on $k$ and $f$ are given for the pointwise and uniform convergence to the Cauchy principal value integral $$\not{\int}^1_{-1} \frac{k(x)f(x)}{x - \lambda} dx, \quad-1 &lt; \lambda &lt; 1,$$ of a sequence of integrals of piecewise linear approximations to $f(x)$ or $g_\lambda(x) = (f(x) - f(\lambda))/(x - \lambda)$. The important special case, $k(x) = (1 - x)^\alpha(1 + x)^\beta$, is considered in detail.</p>
          </abstract>
